# MLX dev machine — merge into docker/env (Mac Apple Silicon).
# oaao stack in Docker; Lance MLX runs on the **host** (Apple GPU), not inside Docker.
#
# Prefer Settings → Multimodal → Lance → **Config** → Worker base URL:
#   http://host.docker.internal:8787
# (persisted in backbone/config/oaaoai/mm_modules.json — hot apply, no orchestrator restart)

LANCE_DEV_BACKEND=mlx

# Optional orchestrator env fallback (used when Settings URL is empty):
# OAAO_LANCE_BASE_URL=http://host.docker.internal:8787
OAAO_LANCE_HOST_PORT=8787

# Do NOT use compose profile lance / lance-cuda on MLX dev — those are CPU/CUDA containers.
# Run your MLX HTTP wrapper on the host bound to 127.0.0.1:8787 with the same routes:
#   GET  /health
#   POST /v1/task  { "task": "x2t_image", "inputs": { "path", "image_url", ... } }
#
# MLX model notes (understanding LLM only — not full ViT pipeline):
#   https://huggingface.co/Reza2kn/Lance-3B-und-MLX-NVFP4
# For true x2t_image you still need ViT / full Lance path or vision LLM fallback.

# Verify from host:
#   curl -s http://127.0.0.1:8787/health
# Verify from orchestrator container:
#   docker exec oaaoai-v1-orchestrator-1 python -c "import urllib.request; print(urllib.request.urlopen('http://host.docker.internal:8787/health').read())"
